Upload the dataframes and alignment (in FASTA) to calculate the pairwise genetic distance matrix:

library("ape") #pairwise distance from DNA sequences
## Warning: package 'ape' was built under R version 4.2.3
library("seqinr") #read alignment 
## Warning: package 'seqinr' was built under R version 4.2.3
## 
## Attaching package: 'seqinr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:ape':
## 
##     as.alignment, consensus
library("FactoMineR") #Principal Component Analysis (PCA)
## Warning: package 'FactoMineR' was built under R version 4.2.3
library("factoextra") #Distance Matrix Computation and Visualization
## Loading required package: ggplot2
## Warning: package 'ggplot2' was built under R version 4.2.3
## Welcome! Want to learn more? See two factoextra-related books at https://goo.gl/ve3WBa
library("corrplot")
## corrplot 0.92 loaded
RVBdistdf <- read.csv("GeneticDistanceMatrix_RV-B_20240621.csv", row.names=1) #the pairwise genetic distance dataframe
RVBmetadf <-read.csv("RVB-PCA_metadata_20240621.csv", row.names=1) #the metadata associated to sequences/individuals
RVBmetadf[RVBmetadf ==''] <- NA
RVBmetadf$AgeGroup <- as.factor(RVBmetadf$AgeGroup)
RVBmetadf$Genotype <- as.factor(RVBmetadf$Genotype)
RVBmetadf$ZipCode <- as.factor(RVBmetadf$ZipCode)
RVBmetadf$Sex <- as.factor(RVBmetadf$Sex)
RVBmetadf$COLLECTION <- as.factor(substr(RVBmetadf$CollectionDate, 1, 7))
RVBmetadf$Clinica <- as.factor(RVBmetadf$Symptoms)
RVBmetadf$Age <- as.numeric(RVBmetadf$Age)
RVBmetadf$RV_Ct_value <- as.numeric(RVBmetadf$RV_Ct_value)

Calculate the eigenvalues and principal component analysis:

#PCA analysis
res.RVB <- PCA(RVBdistdf, scale.unit = TRUE, ncp = 6)

eig.val <- get_eigenvalue(res.RVB)

#To evaluate the number of Principal Components we can see the Scree Plot, which is the plot of the eigenvalues ordered from largest to the smallest.
fviz_eig(res.RVB, addlabels = TRUE, ylim = c(0, 50))

Analysis of quality and contribution of individuals:

fviz_pca_ind(res.RVB, col.ind = "cos2", pointsize = "cos2", gradient.cols = c("#00AFBB", "#E7B800", "#FC4E07"), labelsize=2)

#To visualize the contribution of individuals to the first two principal components:
fviz_contrib(res.RVB, choice = "ind", axes = 1:2, labelsize=2) + theme(text = element_text(size=7))

Constructing a dendrogram and making the hierarchical clustering:

library("dendextend") #cut tree into groups

library("svglite") #save plots
## Warning: package 'svglite' was built under R version 4.2.3
RVBdm<-dist(RVBdistdf, method = 'euclidean') 
RVBhc<-hclust(RVBdm, method="complete") # simple dendrogram

#evaluating the number of clusters such that the total intra-cluster variation (total within-cluster sum of square, WSS) is minimized:
fviz_nbclust(RVBdistdf, FUNcluster=hcut, method="wss") + geom_vline(xintercept = 4, linetype = 2)

cut_cmp <- cutree(RVBhc, k = 4) #applying the clustering by wss
plot(RVBhc, hang=-1, cex=0.2) 
#plot with cluster rectangles within the clusters:
rect.hclust(RVBhc, k=4, border=2:4)

#save plot of dendrogram:
#svglite(filename = "RVB_HC_PCA_euclidean_TEST.svg")
#plot(RVBhc, hang=-1, cex=0.2)

library("rcompanion") #Pairwise tests of independence
## Warning: package 'rcompanion' was built under R version 4.2.3
library("AMR") #G-test
RVB_cluster_pre <- merge(RVBmetadf, cut_cmp, by = 0)
RVB_cluster_pre$y<-as.factor(RVB_cluster_pre$y)
RVB_cluster <- RVB_cluster_pre[!is.na(RVB_cluster_pre$Age),]
RVB_cluster_clinica <- RVB_cluster[!is.na(RVB_cluster$Clinica),]
RVB_cluster_zipcode <- RVB_cluster[!is.na(RVB_cluster$ZipCode),]
RVB_cluster_sex <- RVB_cluster[!is.na(RVB_cluster$Sex),]

g.test(RVB_cluster_clinica$Clinica, RVB_cluster_clinica$y)
## Warning in g.test(RVB_cluster_clinica$Clinica, RVB_cluster_clinica$y):
## G-statistic approximation may be incorrect due to E < 5
## 
##  G-test of independence
## 
## data:  RVB_cluster_clinica$Clinica and RVB_cluster_clinica$y
## X-squared = 2.1097, p-value = 0.55
X1 = pairwiseNominalIndependence(as.matrix(table(RVB_cluster_clinica$Clinica, RVB_cluster_clinica$y)), compare = "column", fisher = FALSE, chisq = FALSE, method = "bonferroni", digits = 3)
cldList(p.adj.Gtest ~ Comparison, data= X1, threshold  = 0.05)
##   Group Letter MonoLetter
## 1     1      a          a
## 2     2      a          a
## 3     3      a          a
## 4     4      a          a
ggplot(RVB_cluster_clinica, aes(x=Clinica, fill=y)) + geom_bar(position = "fill")

g.test(RVB_cluster_zipcode$ZipCode, RVB_cluster_zipcode$y)
## Warning in g.test(RVB_cluster_zipcode$ZipCode, RVB_cluster_zipcode$y):
## G-statistic approximation may be incorrect due to E < 5
## 
##  G-test of independence
## 
## data:  RVB_cluster_zipcode$ZipCode and RVB_cluster_zipcode$y
## X-squared = 60.415, p-value = 0.006597
X2 = pairwiseNominalIndependence(as.matrix(table(RVB_cluster_zipcode$ZipCode, RVB_cluster_zipcode$y)), compare = "column", fisher = FALSE, chisq = FALSE, method = "bonferroni", digits = 3)
cldList(p.adj.Gtest ~ Comparison, data= X2, threshold  = 0.05)
##   Group Letter MonoLetter
## 1     1      a          a
## 2     2      a          a
## 3     3      a          a
## 4     4      a          a
ggplot(RVB_cluster_zipcode, aes(x=ZipCode, fill=y)) + geom_bar(position = "fill") + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) 

X3 = pairwiseNominalIndependence(as.matrix(table(RVB_cluster_sex$Sex, RVB_cluster_sex$y)), compare = "column", fisher = FALSE, chisq = FALSE, method = "bonferroni", digits = 3)
cldList(p.adj.Gtest ~ Comparison, data= X3, threshold  = 0.05)
##   Group Letter MonoLetter
## 1     1      a          a
## 2     2      a          a
## 3     3      a          a
## 4     4      a          a
ggplot(RVB_cluster_sex, aes(x=Sex, fill=y)) + geom_bar(position = "fill")

X4 = pairwiseNominalIndependence(as.matrix(table(RVB_cluster$AgeGroup, RVB_cluster$y)), compare = "column", fisher = FALSE, chisq = FALSE, method = "bonferroni", digits = 3) 
cldList(p.adj.Gtest ~ Comparison, data= X4, threshold  = 0.05)
##   Group Letter MonoLetter
## 1     1      a         a 
## 2     2      b          b
## 3     3      a         a 
## 4     4      a         a
ggplot(RVB_cluster, aes(x=AgeGroup, fill=y)) + geom_bar(position = "fill") + scale_x_discrete(limits = c("<5y", "5-18y", "19-65y", ">65y"))

RVB_cluster_pre$Year <- as.factor(substr(RVB_cluster_pre$CollectionDate, 1, 4))
X5 = pairwiseNominalIndependence(as.matrix(table(RVB_cluster_pre$Year, RVB_cluster_pre$y)), compare = "column", fisher = FALSE, chisq = FALSE, method = "bonferroni", digits = 3)
cldList(p.adj.Gtest ~ Comparison, data= X5, threshold  = 0.05)
##   Group Letter MonoLetter

ggplot(RVB_cluster_pre, aes(x=Year, fill=y)) + geom_bar(position = "fill")

#Further analysis with continuous variables Age and Ct:
#Age
res.kruskal <- RVB_cluster %>% kruskal_test(Age ~ y) #Kruskal-Wallis Test
res.kruskal
## # A tibble: 1 × 6
##   .y.       n statistic    df          p method        
## * <chr> <int>     <dbl> <int>      <dbl> <chr>         
## 1 Age     105      30.1     3 0.00000131 Kruskal-Wallis
#Wilcoxon’s test to calculate pairwise comparisons between group:
pwc <- RVB_cluster %>% 
  wilcox_test(Age ~ y, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni") 
pwc

#visualization: box plots with p-values:
pwc <- pwc %>% add_xy_position(x = "y")
ggboxplot(RVB_cluster, x = "y", y = "Age") +
  stat_pvalue_manual(pwc, hide.ns = TRUE) +
  labs(
    subtitle = get_test_label(res.kruskal, detailed = TRUE),
    caption = get_pwc_label(pwc)
